Revision

In my first submission, I did not include the y axis marks at 0, 40, 80, 120 for the Temperature graph and for the precipitation y axis, the labels were not at 4 and 8. On my first attempt, I didnât think that the marks were as relevant, so I didnât pay much attention to it, but while revising it, I realized how these details make the graph look even better. I learned how the scale_y_continuous and its arguments (labels, limits, expand, etc) works, I knew the general idea of the function but I was not as familiar with how it actually works in practice. Some optional suggestions were to remove the labels on the x axis on the precipitation graph (which I did), and to change the theme for both plots. I decided to keep the theme_clean() because I didnât like how it looked with other themes, the only issue was that when merging both plots, theme_clean() creates grids/frames, making the graph âless flowingâ,if I have this issue in another context, I may used another theme or as a last resource, I would remove those lines on an image editor.

Visualization

#Wrangling 

month_starts <- weather %>% 
  filter(Day==1, Month != 1)

month_m <- weather %>%
  filter(Day ==15 ) %>%
  pull(dateInYear)

recordHighOnly <-  weather %>%
  filter(RecordP) 

recordHighOnlyT <-  weather %>%
  filter(Record) 

recordHighOnlyP <-  weather %>%
  filter(Day == 28) 

ylimits <-  c(0, 40, 80, 120)
# Code for recreating the visualization (Temperature)

temp <-  ggplot(weather) +
  geom_linerange(aes(x= dateInYear, ymin = RecordLow, ymax= RecordHigh ), color= "#ECEBE3")+
  geom_linerange(aes(x= dateInYear, ymin = NormalLow, ymax= NormalHigh ),color= "#C8B8BA")+
  geom_linerange(aes(x= dateInYear,  ymin = Low, ymax= High ),color= "#A90248")+
  geom_vline(data= month_starts,  mapping = aes(xintercept = dateInYear ), lty= "dashed")+
  geom_text_repel(aes(x=dateInYear, y= RecordHigh,label= RecordText, check_overlap= TRUE))+
  geom_point(data =recordHighOnlyT, aes(x= dateInYear,  y= RecordHigh),shape= 25, fill= "black")+
  scale_x_continuous(labels = month.abb ,breaks = month_m)+
  scale_y_continuous(labels = c(0, 40, 80, 120), 
                     limits = c(min(ylimits), max(ylimits)),
                     breaks = ylimits,
                     # expand = expansion(add =c(0, 0))
                     )+
  theme_clean()+
  labs(title = "Temperature",
       x= "",
       y= "")

# Code for recreating the visualization (Precipitation)
Precip <- weather %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = dateInYear, y = CulmPrec ))+
  geom_line(aes(x = dateInYear, y = CulmPrec), color= "#32a3d8")+
  geom_area(fill= "#ebeae2")+
  geom_vline(data= month_starts, mapping = aes(xintercept = dateInYear),color= "grey")+
  geom_point(data =recordHighOnly,aes(x= dateInYear,y=CulmPrec ),shape= 25,fill= "black")+
  geom_text_repel(data=recordHighOnlyP, aes(x=dateInYear, y= CulmPrec, label= CulmPrec,
                                          check_overlap= TRUE))+
  # scale_x_continuous(labels = "")+
  scale_y_continuous(labels = c(4, 8), 
                     # limits = c(min(ylimits_precip), max(ylimits_precip)),

                     limits = c(0, 10)
                     # expand = expansion(add =c(0, 0))
                     )+
  labs(title = "Precipitation",
       x= "",
       y="")+
  theme_clean()+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_blank(), axis.ticks.x = element_blank())
